1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:03,503
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor…</i> ♪

2
00:00:03,586 --> 00:00:06,631
["Mr. Tailor" playing]

3
00:00:08,591 --> 00:00:10,552
- <i>♪ Fix this</i> ♪
- <i>♪ Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

4
00:00:10,635 --> 00:00:12,887
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

5
00:00:12,971 --> 00:00:15,724
♪ <i>One cut, and it's settled</i> ♪

6
00:00:16,808 --> 00:00:19,477
[Atoy] <i>I met a woman on the island.</i>

7
00:00:20,103 --> 00:00:22,147
<i>But she vanished like a bubble.</i>

8
00:00:22,731 --> 00:00:25,525
<i>Then after eight years, we met again.</i>

9
00:00:25,608 --> 00:00:26,651
<i>I thought we were okay.</i>

10
00:00:26,735 --> 00:00:28,278
<i>Turns out, we weren't.</i>

11
00:00:28,361 --> 00:00:30,030
<i>It was only me who thought so.</i>

12
00:00:30,113 --> 00:00:33,783
[Cita] This is the first time
I've seen you brokenhearted.

13
00:00:33,867 --> 00:00:35,702
[Audrey, in English]
<i>He's no longer a mystery.</i>

14
00:00:35,785 --> 00:00:38,121
He's a disappointment and not worth it.

15
00:00:38,872 --> 00:00:39,873
[Gavin, in English] Are you okay?

16
00:00:39,956 --> 00:00:41,416
[doctor] <i>Your appendix is inflamed.</i>

17
00:00:41,499 --> 00:00:43,460
My appendix was already removed.

18
00:00:44,043 --> 00:00:45,712
Here's the scar.

19
00:00:45,795 --> 00:00:48,506
[in English] Ma'am,
that is a low transverse incision.

20
00:00:48,590 --> 00:00:51,676
Or what we call the bikini cut
of a caesarean section.

21
00:00:52,260 --> 00:00:54,512
[Audrey] <i>Are you saying</i>
<i>I was pregnant before?</i>

22
00:00:54,596 --> 00:00:55,597
[doctor] <i>You didn't know?</i>

23
00:00:55,680 --> 00:00:56,765
<i>Could it be they already met?</i>

24
00:00:56,848 --> 00:00:59,267
[Martina] <i>It's better for us,</i>
<i>especially Dad,</i>

25
00:00:59,350 --> 00:01:01,436
<i>that Audrey is not in the Philippines.</i>

26
00:01:01,936 --> 00:01:06,232
We won't have to worry about
that one thing we're hiding from her.

27
00:01:06,816 --> 00:01:08,526
[Audrey] <i>So, what's the truth, Dad?</i>

28
00:01:08,610 --> 00:01:10,361
Was I pregnant then?

29
00:01:10,945 --> 00:01:11,780
[in English] Yes.

30
00:01:11,863 --> 00:01:12,989
PREVIOUSLY

31
00:01:13,073 --> 00:01:14,616
You were pregnant then.

32
00:01:19,412 --> 00:01:21,331
[music fades]

33
00:01:21,414 --> 00:01:22,582
Dad…

34
00:01:23,750 --> 00:01:24,584
‪[dramatic sting]

35
00:01:24,959 --> 00:01:26,252
Dad…

36
00:01:26,336 --> 00:01:28,922
[tense music playing]

37
00:01:29,547 --> 00:01:30,548
[shaky breathing]

38
00:01:32,592 --> 00:01:34,844
Why didn't you tell me?

39
00:01:37,138 --> 00:01:38,389
[in English] I'm sorry, child.

40
00:01:38,473 --> 00:01:39,641
We had our reasons.

41
00:01:39,724 --> 00:01:40,892
[Audrey] We?!

42
00:01:41,601 --> 00:01:43,603
‪[gasping, sighs]

43
00:01:45,438 --> 00:01:46,815
Who are "we"?

44
00:01:48,358 --> 00:01:52,195
I see no reason why you
had to hide this from me.

45
00:01:52,278 --> 00:01:54,322
You know, dear, I'm sorry.

46
00:01:54,405 --> 00:01:56,991
We didn't know you would wake up then.

47
00:01:57,075 --> 00:01:58,451
Well, now that I'm awake,

48
00:01:58,535 --> 00:02:01,371
I want to know everything!

49
00:02:04,124 --> 00:02:05,125
Where is my child?

50
00:02:05,959 --> 00:02:07,377
[music swells]

51
00:02:07,460 --> 00:02:09,170
Where is my child?!

52
00:02:09,712 --> 00:02:13,800
[groaning]

53
00:02:14,551 --> 00:02:16,719
[Dmitri] Nurse? Nurse!

54
00:02:19,514 --> 00:02:20,932
[pained breathing]

55
00:02:21,015 --> 00:02:22,183
[in English] Can you call a doctor?

56
00:02:22,267 --> 00:02:23,601
[in English] Call a doctor!

57
00:02:23,685 --> 00:02:25,645
Hurry! Call a doctor!

58
00:02:26,938 --> 00:02:28,314
[music fades]

59
00:02:28,398 --> 00:02:31,276
[suave theme music playing]

60
00:02:57,719 --> 00:02:59,721
[music fades]

61
00:03:12,358 --> 00:03:14,819
[ominous music playing]

62
00:03:26,623 --> 00:03:29,125
I already called Red, and he's on the way.

63
00:03:31,294 --> 00:03:33,212
You both assured me…

64
00:03:34,464 --> 00:03:36,925
that this day would never come.

65
00:03:37,008 --> 00:03:38,843
[tense sting]

66
00:03:38,927 --> 00:03:40,345
But we never told anyone.

67
00:03:40,428 --> 00:03:41,429
No one!

68
00:03:42,180 --> 00:03:44,307
[in English] But she found out on her own…

69
00:03:45,934 --> 00:03:48,770
Because you didn't think
of other possible ways

70
00:03:48,853 --> 00:03:52,065
she could discover what we're hiding.

71
00:03:52,148 --> 00:03:53,775
[pensive music playing]

72
00:03:53,858 --> 00:03:55,652
She's looking for her child.

73
00:03:56,402 --> 00:03:58,196
What should I tell her?

74
00:04:00,573 --> 00:04:02,867
Maybe tell her the child is gone?

75
00:04:03,660 --> 00:04:07,789
I'm sure the child is with somebody now,
or maybe dead.

76
00:04:07,872 --> 00:04:10,708
Then show me the death certificate,

77
00:04:10,792 --> 00:04:12,168
the grave!

78
00:04:13,586 --> 00:04:16,631
Give me details,
so I can answer her properly!

79
00:04:17,799 --> 00:04:23,763
If not, find the child wherever she is.

80
00:04:24,806 --> 00:04:29,018
[in English] You still have time,
since my daughter is in the OR.

81
00:04:29,894 --> 00:04:33,439
[in English] I want
concrete answers within the day.

82
00:04:34,315 --> 00:04:37,402
[sinister music playing]

83
00:04:37,902 --> 00:04:39,362
Martina…

84
00:04:40,154 --> 00:04:41,197
Dad?

85
00:04:43,866 --> 00:04:46,661
Don't mess with me.

86
00:04:48,121 --> 00:04:49,414
[in English] Of course, Dad.

87
00:05:03,219 --> 00:05:04,554
[music fades]

88
00:05:05,471 --> 00:05:08,891
Uh, what are we doing here?

89
00:05:10,101 --> 00:05:12,437
We're meeting my mother's friend.

90
00:05:12,520 --> 00:05:14,188
Her former co-teacher.

91
00:05:15,064 --> 00:05:16,941
[pensive music playing]

92
00:05:17,025 --> 00:05:18,651
[woman] Atoy!

93
00:05:19,277 --> 00:05:21,029
- [Atoy] Oh?
- How are you?

94
00:05:21,112 --> 00:05:22,613
- Still sewing?
- [Atoy chuckles]

95
00:05:22,697 --> 00:05:24,657
Ah, yes. Yes, ma'am. I'm fine.

96
00:05:24,741 --> 00:05:26,743
Uh, this is who I was talking about.

97
00:05:26,826 --> 00:05:28,786
This is Ibyang.

98
00:05:28,870 --> 00:05:32,957
Ibyang, this is Mrs. Feliz Valencia.

99
00:05:33,041 --> 00:05:35,209
She's the one I told you about.

100
00:05:35,293 --> 00:05:38,755
She'll help you study here.

101
00:05:38,838 --> 00:05:42,383
Ah, I'm going to school?

102
00:05:42,467 --> 00:05:44,385
[in English] Surprise!

103
00:05:44,469 --> 00:05:47,096
[in English] Welcome
to your student girl era!

104
00:05:47,180 --> 00:05:48,931
You're on another level now, Ibyang!

105
00:05:49,015 --> 00:05:50,516
[pensive music playing]

106
00:05:50,600 --> 00:05:52,101
[Feliz, in English] Hi, Ibyang!

107
00:05:52,685 --> 00:05:56,147
We'll assess you first
to know your grade level.

108
00:05:56,230 --> 00:05:58,566
Just tests in different subjects.

109
00:05:58,649 --> 00:06:00,234
Come on. Hmm?

110
00:06:00,318 --> 00:06:03,863
Ah, uh… I… I don't want to.

111
00:06:03,946 --> 00:06:06,074
Uh… I don't want to go to school.

112
00:06:06,657 --> 00:06:08,409
- [Feliz] Huh? Hey, wait.
- All right, I'm out of here.

113
00:06:08,493 --> 00:06:09,911
- [Ame] Ibyang!
- Psst, hey…

114
00:06:10,703 --> 00:06:12,163
[mutters] Wait a minute.

115
00:06:13,498 --> 00:06:16,709
- [Ibyant panting]
- [tense music playing]

116
00:06:19,337 --> 00:06:21,631
[Ibyang gasps]

117
00:06:21,714 --> 00:06:24,258
[Atoy, in English] Psst, hey.
Ah. Excuse me.

118
00:06:25,968 --> 00:06:27,178
[Atoy] Uh…

119
00:06:27,261 --> 00:06:28,638
[in English] Excuse me,
excuse me, excuse me.

120
00:06:28,721 --> 00:06:33,601
[sneaky music playing]

121
00:06:34,560 --> 00:06:35,853
[girl] Oh, frog!

122
00:06:38,356 --> 00:06:40,066
My tumbler!

123
00:06:47,573 --> 00:06:48,741
Hey!

124
00:06:50,118 --> 00:06:50,993
Damn you!

125
00:06:52,203 --> 00:06:54,664
Got you. You didn't apologize to me.

126
00:06:55,540 --> 00:06:57,792
You dropped my tumbler in the canal!

127
00:06:58,459 --> 00:06:59,669
[in English] Sorry!

128
00:06:59,752 --> 00:07:01,629
I was just in a hurry.

129
00:07:01,712 --> 00:07:03,798
What about my tumbler?

130
00:07:03,881 --> 00:07:05,383
I can't use it anymore!

131
00:07:05,466 --> 00:07:08,427
[rousing music playing]

132
00:07:12,056 --> 00:07:13,307
[Martina, in English] What the heck?

133
00:07:13,391 --> 00:07:14,559
What took you so long?

134
00:07:14,642 --> 00:07:16,769
I got stuck in traffic.
Did you talk to Dad?

135
00:07:16,853 --> 00:07:17,937
Talk?

136
00:07:18,020 --> 00:07:20,189
More like got burned by a dragon's fire!

137
00:07:20,273 --> 00:07:22,316
[in English] He wants us
to find Audrey's kid.

138
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:23,776
[sinister music playing]

139
00:07:23,860 --> 00:07:25,069
We don't need to do that.

140
00:07:25,153 --> 00:07:28,364
[in English] I know, but we still have to
find where and what happened to that kid.

141
00:07:29,365 --> 00:07:32,368
Just say she's in America or… dead.

142
00:07:32,452 --> 00:07:34,996
I already thought of that.
But it's hard to stick with that,

143
00:07:35,079 --> 00:07:37,331
because Audrey might look
for the grave or the child.

144
00:07:37,415 --> 00:07:39,709
[in English] It would be easy
if the child was really dead.

145
00:07:40,293 --> 00:07:42,962
But it's better
if we know the real answers,

146
00:07:43,045 --> 00:07:45,339
and from there, we can improvise.

147
00:07:47,467 --> 00:07:48,468
[in English] Yeah.

148
00:07:49,302 --> 00:07:51,304
[music fades]

149
00:07:54,765 --> 00:07:55,766
Ah, sir.

150
00:07:55,850 --> 00:08:00,771
Ah, did you see a girl
in a pink printed dress?

151
00:08:02,023 --> 00:08:04,192
A man is looking for you.

152
00:08:04,775 --> 00:08:06,068
Why are you hiding from him?

153
00:08:06,652 --> 00:08:09,614
Just because! Don't point me out, okay?

154
00:08:10,740 --> 00:08:12,700
Pay me first for my tumbler.

155
00:08:13,201 --> 00:08:14,660
It costs 700.

156
00:08:14,744 --> 00:08:17,288
Do I look like I have 700?

157
00:08:18,039 --> 00:08:21,000
Besides, you can just wash it!

158
00:08:21,083 --> 00:08:22,043
[pensive music playing]

159
00:08:22,126 --> 00:08:23,044
Thanks.

160
00:08:28,049 --> 00:08:29,967
- So that's it. Follow me.
- [gasps]

161
00:08:30,593 --> 00:08:31,761
[girl] Sir!

162
00:08:32,803 --> 00:08:33,930
- Sir! Here!
- [Ibyang exclaims]

163
00:08:34,013 --> 00:08:35,932
- [Ibyang] Shh! Don't.
- [girl] Hey.

164
00:08:36,015 --> 00:08:38,768
The girl you're looking for,
she's hiding there.

165
00:08:39,519 --> 00:08:41,604
You're so annoying!

166
00:08:44,106 --> 00:08:45,566
You even ran away, huh?!

167
00:08:46,192 --> 00:08:47,235
Thanks.

168
00:08:48,319 --> 00:08:50,238
Sir, is this your daughter?

169
00:08:50,321 --> 00:08:52,907
She pushed my water bottle into the canal.

170
00:08:52,990 --> 00:08:55,326
Just pay me. It's 1,000.

171
00:08:55,409 --> 00:08:57,370
[sneaky music playing]

172
00:08:57,453 --> 00:08:58,704
Are you kidding?

173
00:08:59,330 --> 00:09:01,832
Earlier, it was only 700.

174
00:09:03,793 --> 00:09:05,545
No, she's not my daughter!

175
00:09:06,212 --> 00:09:07,630
So, I won't pay for that.

176
00:09:08,548 --> 00:09:10,841
Just wash it. It'll be fine!

177
00:09:10,925 --> 00:09:12,385
Well, see that?

178
00:09:12,468 --> 00:09:14,595
You thought you could scam us.

179
00:09:26,357 --> 00:09:27,316
[music fades]

180
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:28,734
And you!

181
00:09:28,818 --> 00:09:30,653
What's the matter with you?
Why don't you want to study?

182
00:09:30,736 --> 00:09:32,113
This is for you.

183
00:09:33,197 --> 00:09:34,740
Because, master…

184
00:09:34,824 --> 00:09:36,742
[gentle music playing]

185
00:09:36,826 --> 00:09:39,287
They'll just laugh at me in school.

186
00:09:39,954 --> 00:09:41,831
They'll find out that

187
00:09:41,914 --> 00:09:44,709
I don't know how to read or write.

188
00:09:45,459 --> 00:09:46,711
What do you want?

189
00:09:47,211 --> 00:09:50,423
For them to laugh at you forever,
because you never studied?

190
00:09:51,007 --> 00:09:52,174
Do you want that?

191
00:09:52,675 --> 00:09:56,137
Then, if you don't know the answer,
you'll just stuff bread in your mouth,

192
00:09:56,220 --> 00:09:58,014
so it won't look like
you're making things up?

193
00:09:58,931 --> 00:10:00,141
You're too harsh on me.

194
00:10:00,224 --> 00:10:01,892
No, because the world really is harsh.

195
00:10:01,976 --> 00:10:04,061
Especially if you have no education!

196
00:10:04,854 --> 00:10:06,606
You will really suffer!

197
00:10:08,441 --> 00:10:10,234
Ibyang, that's why I want you to study.

198
00:10:10,943 --> 00:10:11,861
Huh?

199
00:10:11,944 --> 00:10:14,030
Education is very important.

200
00:10:14,113 --> 00:10:15,740
You can do it.

201
00:10:16,616 --> 00:10:18,784
You're a hustler. You can do it!

202
00:10:18,868 --> 00:10:20,786
I believe in you.

203
00:10:21,662 --> 00:10:22,830
So?

204
00:10:22,913 --> 00:10:23,873
The principal is my friend.

205
00:10:24,498 --> 00:10:27,960
She's my friend.
She can help you, guide you.

206
00:10:28,044 --> 00:10:29,128
Too bad if we miss the opportunity.

207
00:10:30,254 --> 00:10:31,881
So? Please say yes.

208
00:10:33,215 --> 00:10:34,050
[sentimental music playing]

209
00:10:34,133 --> 00:10:35,384
[Atoy] Come on.

210
00:10:45,770 --> 00:10:48,356
Good thing Tonet and Queenie
were rescued, right?

211
00:10:48,439 --> 00:10:50,274
It just so happened
that our own town mates

212
00:10:50,358 --> 00:10:51,901
were victims of the kidnapper.

213
00:10:51,984 --> 00:10:54,779
And thank goodness, I'm not girly!

214
00:10:54,862 --> 00:10:57,990
Because if I were,
I'd be the third victim!

215
00:10:58,074 --> 00:10:59,784
[in English] Afraid of me!

216
00:10:59,867 --> 00:11:00,701
- [Karla, indistinct]
- Wow!

217
00:11:00,785 --> 00:11:02,662
You feel embarrassed, T-Bak?

218
00:11:02,745 --> 00:11:03,746
[all chuckle]

219
00:11:03,829 --> 00:11:05,331
You're hard to kidnap!

220
00:11:05,414 --> 00:11:06,332
- Try it then.
- [boy] Oh, look.

221
00:11:06,415 --> 00:11:07,625
[lively chatter]

222
00:11:07,708 --> 00:11:09,085
[sneaky music playing]

223
00:11:09,168 --> 00:11:10,002
You're so heavy, oh, oh, oh!

224
00:11:10,086 --> 00:11:11,253
[overlapping chatter]

225
00:11:11,337 --> 00:11:12,463
[T-Bak] Wait!

226
00:11:12,546 --> 00:11:15,800
- [Karla] Easy, boss.
- I'll just do IF for one month, okay!

227
00:11:15,883 --> 00:11:17,968
You won't recognize me once I lose weight!

228
00:11:18,052 --> 00:11:21,597
- [Karla] Really?
- And you, Karla, stop pretending!

229
00:11:21,680 --> 00:11:25,559
You just want to be kidnapped
so Gavin will rescue you!

230
00:11:25,643 --> 00:11:28,562
[teasing and chuckling]

231
00:11:28,646 --> 00:11:30,189
Why did the conversation go there?

232
00:11:30,272 --> 00:11:32,191
C'mon! You're just pretending!

233
00:11:32,274 --> 00:11:34,902
You even look for him
when he's not at the court.

234
00:11:34,985 --> 00:11:36,529
- [Karla] Oh, you!
- [boy shrieks]

235
00:11:36,612 --> 00:11:37,988
[girl, in English] That's my car!

236
00:11:38,072 --> 00:11:40,741
[tense music playing]

237
00:11:45,204 --> 00:11:46,914
- Oh, no.
- Boss.

238
00:11:46,997 --> 00:11:48,207
[music fades]

239
00:11:49,041 --> 00:11:50,167
[Emerson grunts]

240
00:11:52,002 --> 00:11:53,003
[Emerson] Huh?

241
00:11:56,382 --> 00:11:57,591
So clean.

242
00:11:57,675 --> 00:12:00,386
[pleasant music playing]

243
00:12:00,469 --> 00:12:01,387
[Tonet humming]

244
00:12:01,470 --> 00:12:03,848
Oh, Tonet?

245
00:12:03,931 --> 00:12:05,182
What are you doing?

246
00:12:06,976 --> 00:12:09,145
Just a little makeover, hmm.

247
00:12:09,228 --> 00:12:11,605
To make this place brighter.

248
00:12:11,689 --> 00:12:13,274
So, when your customers come in,

249
00:12:13,357 --> 00:12:15,317
they'll feel good vibes right away!

250
00:12:15,901 --> 00:12:17,528
- Oh. Brother, wait.
- Oh…

251
00:12:17,611 --> 00:12:18,737
You should have called me.

252
00:12:18,821 --> 00:12:19,780
- No.
- It's fine, it's fine,

253
00:12:19,864 --> 00:12:21,157
- it's fine, it's fine.
- Wait, wait.

254
00:12:21,240 --> 00:12:22,199
[Emerson grunts]

255
00:12:23,367 --> 00:12:25,619
You shouldn't have… bothered.

256
00:12:25,703 --> 00:12:27,288
Thanks, but…

257
00:12:27,371 --> 00:12:28,873
Look, you don't need to do that.

258
00:12:28,956 --> 00:12:30,875
You might end up spending your money here.

259
00:12:31,584 --> 00:12:34,211
Brother, this isn't just for you.

260
00:12:34,295 --> 00:12:35,838
It's for me too.

261
00:12:37,214 --> 00:12:38,174
Huh?

262
00:12:39,341 --> 00:12:40,968
Ah, because…

263
00:12:41,051 --> 00:12:43,637
Because I'll live here now, yes.

264
00:12:43,721 --> 00:12:47,057
And I'll also be your assistant.

265
00:12:47,141 --> 00:12:48,392
Do you want that?

266
00:12:51,353 --> 00:12:53,814
Miss, sorry. We didn't mean it.

267
00:12:53,898 --> 00:12:55,316
We were just teasing.

268
00:12:55,983 --> 00:12:57,318
[in English] I noticed.

269
00:12:57,401 --> 00:12:58,944
But something broke!

270
00:12:59,028 --> 00:13:00,154
And it got dirty.

271
00:13:00,237 --> 00:13:02,114
Ah, we'll just clean it, okay?

272
00:13:02,198 --> 00:13:03,699
Ah, um, don't.

273
00:13:04,909 --> 00:13:06,911
It might get dirtier.

274
00:13:06,994 --> 00:13:08,287
[tense sting]

275
00:13:08,370 --> 00:13:09,830
Oh, no!

276
00:13:09,914 --> 00:13:11,957
My fog lamp is broken!

277
00:13:13,334 --> 00:13:15,836
I won't charge you, since…

278
00:13:16,337 --> 00:13:18,923
[in English] I don't think you guys
can afford to pay it anyway.

279
00:13:19,423 --> 00:13:21,467
[sneaky music playing]

280
00:13:21,550 --> 00:13:22,593
How much is it?

281
00:13:23,177 --> 00:13:24,053
We'll chip in!

282
00:13:24,136 --> 00:13:25,054
- Yes.
- Mmm.

283
00:13:25,137 --> 00:13:27,306
It's not like that fog lamp
costs one million, right?

284
00:13:27,389 --> 00:13:28,516
- Exactly.
- [scoffs]

285
00:13:28,599 --> 00:13:29,892
Whoa!

286
00:13:29,975 --> 00:13:31,519
[in English] I don't like your tone.

287
00:13:32,102 --> 00:13:34,480
[in English] Or your outfit.

288
00:13:35,481 --> 00:13:37,983
But because I'm kind,

289
00:13:38,067 --> 00:13:40,361
I'll just take your…

290
00:13:40,444 --> 00:13:42,071
ball as payment!

291
00:13:43,280 --> 00:13:44,323
Uh…

292
00:13:44,406 --> 00:13:45,866
- [T-Bak] Let's give it.
- [girl] Well?

293
00:13:45,950 --> 00:13:51,288
Will you give it, or pay
for the damage and car wash?

294
00:13:51,372 --> 00:13:53,374
Let's just give it, because otherwise…

295
00:13:53,457 --> 00:13:54,959
She might hurt us.

296
00:13:55,042 --> 00:13:56,126
- Yes. Agree, friend.
- Let's give it.

297
00:13:56,210 --> 00:13:57,586
I don't have money either.

298
00:13:57,670 --> 00:13:59,421
But this has sentimental value.

299
00:13:59,505 --> 00:14:01,507
It's what wins us bets!

300
00:14:02,883 --> 00:14:03,884
Yes.

301
00:14:03,968 --> 00:14:05,553
She's pretty, right?
Do you think she's taken?

302
00:14:05,636 --> 00:14:06,720
I don't know about you!

303
00:14:06,804 --> 00:14:08,055
- [indistinct]
- [girl sighs] Oh, no!

304
00:14:08,138 --> 00:14:09,598
- You're taking so long to decide.
- [T-Bak] Oh!

305
00:14:09,682 --> 00:14:11,642
I'm sure you'll give it anyway, right?

306
00:14:11,725 --> 00:14:12,685
Thanks!

307
00:14:15,437 --> 00:14:16,814
Our ball.

308
00:14:17,815 --> 00:14:20,067
It's your fault! Why did you duck?

309
00:14:20,860 --> 00:14:22,611
I would've been hit.

310
00:14:23,237 --> 00:14:25,197
I've already assessed her capacity,

311
00:14:25,281 --> 00:14:27,157
and I'll put her in grade 1.

312
00:14:27,241 --> 00:14:29,618
After a few months,
she can take a test again.

313
00:14:29,702 --> 00:14:31,287
And if the results are good,

314
00:14:31,370 --> 00:14:33,998
she will be accelerated to her age group.

315
00:14:34,081 --> 00:14:34,999
[scoffs]

316
00:14:35,082 --> 00:14:36,208
Thank you, ma'am.

317
00:14:36,709 --> 00:14:37,626
[Feliz, in English] You're welcome.

318
00:14:37,710 --> 00:14:40,504
Also, where are Ibyang's parents?

319
00:14:41,171 --> 00:14:42,006
Uh…

320
00:14:42,089 --> 00:14:43,507
I don't have parents.

321
00:14:43,591 --> 00:14:44,425
[somber music playing]

322
00:14:44,508 --> 00:14:46,969
I grew up in an orphanage.

323
00:14:47,052 --> 00:14:47,970
Okay, Ibyang.

324
00:14:48,053 --> 00:14:49,305
Just play there.

325
00:14:49,805 --> 00:14:53,058
Atoy, are they dead?

326
00:14:53,684 --> 00:14:55,394
Can you at least give me their names?

327
00:14:55,477 --> 00:14:58,606
[in English] This is
for school registration purposes.

328
00:14:58,689 --> 00:15:01,025
Ibyang is an abandoned child.

329
00:15:01,692 --> 00:15:05,362
Ah, maybe we can follow up later
with her certificate of foundling.

330
00:15:05,446 --> 00:15:08,157
We'll request it from the agency tomorrow.

331
00:15:08,240 --> 00:15:11,452
Okay. I can put your name
as guardian in her school records.

332
00:15:11,535 --> 00:15:13,787
So she can start tomorrow.

333
00:15:13,871 --> 00:15:15,748
Doesn't the orphanage have a copy?

334
00:15:16,624 --> 00:15:20,294
No, ma'am. It's hard
to request papers from…

335
00:15:20,377 --> 00:15:22,296
the orphanage she came from.

336
00:15:22,379 --> 00:15:23,672
Why is that?

337
00:15:25,758 --> 00:15:29,845
[sinister music playing]

338
00:15:29,929 --> 00:15:31,764
Come. Sit, sit down.

339
00:15:31,847 --> 00:15:33,807
Sit here for a while.
Come here, come here.

340
00:15:33,891 --> 00:15:34,975
[Emerson sighs]

341
00:15:36,185 --> 00:15:37,645
Tonet,

342
00:15:38,228 --> 00:15:41,649
of course, I really want you here with me.

343
00:15:41,732 --> 00:15:43,359
I missed you.

344
00:15:44,568 --> 00:15:48,113
But look… Look at my setup here, right?

345
00:15:48,614 --> 00:15:51,533
It's so small, and there's
only one room, so cramped.

346
00:15:51,617 --> 00:15:52,826
[Emerson inhales]

347
00:15:52,910 --> 00:15:55,746
You know, it might be better…

348
00:15:55,829 --> 00:15:58,457
if you stay first with Miss Cita.

349
00:15:58,540 --> 00:16:00,376
That's close by, right?

350
00:16:00,459 --> 00:16:02,628
And also,

351
00:16:02,711 --> 00:16:04,964
don't give up your job at Atoy's shop.

352
00:16:05,047 --> 00:16:06,048
[gentle music playing]

353
00:16:06,131 --> 00:16:08,300
At least there you have a salary.

354
00:16:08,384 --> 00:16:10,302
Here, what can I give you?

355
00:16:10,386 --> 00:16:11,428
Scraps?

356
00:16:13,555 --> 00:16:14,723
Eh…

357
00:16:14,807 --> 00:16:16,058
Okay, fine!

358
00:16:16,141 --> 00:16:18,894
Just let me visit you
here every day, okay?

359
00:16:18,978 --> 00:16:20,437
- Yes!
- I'll do the cleaning.

360
00:16:20,521 --> 00:16:23,107
You can hang out here all day,

361
00:16:23,190 --> 00:16:24,483
- doing whatever…
- [Jason] Tonet?

362
00:16:25,776 --> 00:16:26,652
[in English] Hi!

363
00:16:26,735 --> 00:16:28,570
[in English] I heard what happened.

364
00:16:28,654 --> 00:16:30,197
[in English] I'm just so glad
you're back safe.

365
00:16:30,280 --> 00:16:31,865
[quirky music playing]

366
00:16:31,949 --> 00:16:36,662
Who is this speaking
in friends of English?

367
00:16:36,745 --> 00:16:39,415
Hello, sir! I'm Jason.

368
00:16:39,498 --> 00:16:41,166
[in English] Tonet's friend.

369
00:16:41,250 --> 00:16:42,710
[in English] Hopefully,
more than that soon.

370
00:16:42,793 --> 00:16:44,253
[chuckles]

371
00:16:44,336 --> 00:16:45,546
Ah…

372
00:16:45,629 --> 00:16:46,714
[Paldo] Emerson?

373
00:16:46,797 --> 00:16:48,382
Emerson, is Tonet there?

374
00:16:48,465 --> 00:16:50,092
[quirky music continues]

375
00:16:52,845 --> 00:16:54,471
[Tonet titters]

376
00:16:55,180 --> 00:16:57,307
Uh, Tonet…

377
00:16:57,891 --> 00:16:59,768
- Uh, Paldo. Uh.
- [Paldo] I cooked for you.

378
00:17:00,769 --> 00:17:01,895
[in English] Who are you?

379
00:17:03,022 --> 00:17:04,148
Huh?

380
00:17:04,982 --> 00:17:07,401
[Paldo chuckles sarcastically]

381
00:17:07,484 --> 00:17:08,777
[Paldo] This one's something else, huh?

382
00:17:08,861 --> 00:17:10,154
Asking who I am?

383
00:17:11,155 --> 00:17:13,157
[in English] You don't know me?

384
00:17:14,408 --> 00:17:15,617
Emerson!

385
00:17:16,410 --> 00:17:18,996
Is this twisted-tongue guy a customer?

386
00:17:19,830 --> 00:17:21,457
Looks like he can't pay.

387
00:17:22,374 --> 00:17:23,500
Just like you sometimes, right?

388
00:17:24,209 --> 00:17:25,085
[Emerson smirks]

389
00:17:25,169 --> 00:17:27,379
Uh… Ah…

390
00:17:27,463 --> 00:17:31,133
Speaking in friends
of, uh, English of Tonet.

391
00:17:31,216 --> 00:17:32,051
[Paldo] Ah!

392
00:17:32,676 --> 00:17:34,762
[music fades]

393
00:17:34,845 --> 00:17:39,808
[laughing]

394
00:17:39,892 --> 00:17:41,727
- [Tonet] Ah, Brother! Yes.
- [Emerson chuckles]

395
00:17:41,810 --> 00:17:43,145
[Tonet] It's fine, yes.

396
00:17:43,228 --> 00:17:46,523
Sorry, yes. You, you…

397
00:17:46,607 --> 00:17:47,483
Go outside.

398
00:17:47,566 --> 00:17:49,902
Go outside for cockfighting,
then stare at each other.

399
00:17:49,985 --> 00:17:52,237
Because I just cleaned the f-floor, floor!

400
00:17:52,321 --> 00:17:53,947
[in English] I just cleaned it! [laughs]

401
00:17:54,031 --> 00:17:57,451
Yes! You go out and leave, okay! Yes.

402
00:17:57,534 --> 00:18:01,038
Because, sorry, I'm taken. Yes. I'm taken.

403
00:18:01,121 --> 00:18:03,832
I have TTH, TTH! Reserved…

404
00:18:04,583 --> 00:18:05,876
Ah… You too!

405
00:18:05,959 --> 00:18:07,544
Yes, go out too!

406
00:18:07,628 --> 00:18:08,462
- [laughs]
- Me too?

407
00:18:08,545 --> 00:18:10,798
- Yes! I'm taken, yes.
- [chuckles]

408
00:18:10,881 --> 00:18:12,424
Thank you, Paldo!

409
00:18:12,508 --> 00:18:14,760
Yes, I'm reserved for my TTH!

410
00:18:14,843 --> 00:18:16,303
Yes. Thank you!

411
00:18:16,386 --> 00:18:18,806
[sneaky music playing]

412
00:18:18,889 --> 00:18:20,891
Your hair is so long,
you might trip when you go out.

413
00:18:20,974 --> 00:18:21,809
Look, oh. So long, oh.

414
00:18:21,892 --> 00:18:23,268
- [Tonet titters]
- Your hair is so long.

415
00:18:23,352 --> 00:18:24,353
[Tonet titters]

416
00:18:25,938 --> 00:18:27,022
[Emerson] Hmm…

417
00:18:35,405 --> 00:18:38,283
Hon, I just called social services,

418
00:18:38,367 --> 00:18:40,494
because I couldn't find
the orphanage's number.

419
00:18:41,286 --> 00:18:42,496
[in English] And guess what?

420
00:18:42,579 --> 00:18:44,123
The orphanage burned down two years ago.

421
00:18:44,206 --> 00:18:47,584
[in English] All the records of kids
adopted eight years ago, gone.

422
00:18:47,668 --> 00:18:50,129
[in English] Even their
current records, burned.

423
00:18:50,212 --> 00:18:51,505
[in English] Problem solved, then!

424
00:18:52,005 --> 00:18:53,090
[in English] What do you mean?

425
00:18:53,674 --> 00:18:55,217
[in English] We can't tell Dad about this!

426
00:18:55,300 --> 00:18:56,218
[tense music playing]

427
00:18:56,301 --> 00:18:59,138
He'll be more furious
and find a way to look for the child!

428
00:18:59,221 --> 00:19:01,723
And he once mentioned he knew…

429
00:19:01,807 --> 00:19:03,892
[in English] I don't know,
a man hunter or something?

430
00:19:04,685 --> 00:19:07,688
So, this Master Cutter is a tracker?

431
00:19:07,771 --> 00:19:08,939
Not a tailor?

432
00:19:09,022 --> 00:19:10,482
[suspicious music playing]

433
00:19:10,566 --> 00:19:13,277
[Dmitri, in English] Yes,
and that's his code name.

434
00:19:13,360 --> 00:19:14,736
[in English] Don't ask me why.

435
00:19:16,113 --> 00:19:18,157
He doesn't just find people.

436
00:19:20,075 --> 00:19:23,954
The Kelso I asked you to find for months,

437
00:19:24,538 --> 00:19:25,789
which you couldn't,

438
00:19:26,623 --> 00:19:28,250
he found it in one week.

439
00:19:29,668 --> 00:19:30,919
The Master Cutter.

440
00:19:32,045 --> 00:19:33,255
He must not get ahead of us.

441
00:19:34,381 --> 00:19:35,299
[in English] Exactly.

442
00:19:35,382 --> 00:19:37,718
We'll lose control
when your father gets involved.

443
00:19:37,801 --> 00:19:40,554
We need to find a way,
so they don't find the child.

444
00:19:42,639 --> 00:19:43,724
What's your plan?

445
00:19:43,807 --> 00:19:46,310
[in English] First, I have to get in touch
with the head of the orphanage.

446
00:19:46,393 --> 00:19:47,519
The one I gave the baby to.

447
00:19:47,603 --> 00:19:51,064
And then from there, I'll find a way
for us to get the upper hand.

448
00:19:52,107 --> 00:19:53,066
Okay.

449
00:19:53,650 --> 00:19:54,526
Okay.

450
00:20:01,742 --> 00:20:04,578
Hey, Ibyang, go to sleep now.
You still have school tomorrow.

451
00:20:05,996 --> 00:20:07,497
[gentle music playing]

452
00:20:07,581 --> 00:20:09,291
Uh, but…

453
00:20:10,167 --> 00:20:11,001
Never mind.

454
00:20:12,211 --> 00:20:14,713
- [Atoy] Why?
- What if…

455
00:20:15,214 --> 00:20:17,341
the kids don't like me?

456
00:20:18,717 --> 00:20:20,594
What if they're mean?

457
00:20:22,304 --> 00:20:23,513
Ibyang…

458
00:20:25,390 --> 00:20:28,227
It's normal to have negative thoughts.

459
00:20:28,727 --> 00:20:31,063
It's normal to think of those things.

460
00:20:31,146 --> 00:20:36,193
Sometimes those negative thoughts
are even very long, right?

461
00:20:38,695 --> 00:20:40,530
Like this, like…

462
00:20:41,490 --> 00:20:43,033
Like thread.

463
00:20:45,953 --> 00:20:47,287
Think about it.

464
00:20:47,371 --> 00:20:50,290
Think of this
as your negative thoughts, Ibyang.

465
00:20:50,374 --> 00:20:51,625
It's long, right?

466
00:20:51,708 --> 00:20:53,418
You imagine so many things.

467
00:20:53,502 --> 00:20:56,380
They're very long, and then…

468
00:20:57,214 --> 00:20:58,840
this needle…

469
00:20:59,675 --> 00:21:01,551
This needle is your mind.

470
00:21:01,635 --> 00:21:03,136
This is your brain.

471
00:21:04,471 --> 00:21:07,683
Naturally, it will enter your mind.

472
00:21:07,766 --> 00:21:08,892
When it enters…

473
00:21:09,810 --> 00:21:11,895
just let it pass through.

474
00:21:11,979 --> 00:21:14,189
Let it pass and pass,

475
00:21:15,565 --> 00:21:17,693
and don't stop, so it won't get stuck.

476
00:21:18,485 --> 00:21:19,695
Remember.

477
00:21:20,279 --> 00:21:23,448
It passes, but it doesn't stay.

478
00:21:23,532 --> 00:21:25,200
What if…

479
00:21:25,701 --> 00:21:27,452
it gets tangled?

480
00:21:31,248 --> 00:21:32,582
If it's tangled…

481
00:21:34,209 --> 00:21:35,043
Chook.

482
00:21:36,003 --> 00:21:37,045
You cut it…

483
00:21:38,338 --> 00:21:40,090
and it should come from you.

484
00:21:42,968 --> 00:21:46,013
[dreamy music playing]

485
00:21:46,096 --> 00:21:47,097
[chuckles softly]

486
00:21:49,474 --> 00:21:51,518
- I'm sleepy now.
- [Atoy, in English] Very good.

487
00:21:51,601 --> 00:21:53,353
- Okay, go to sleep now.
- I'll go to bed now, okay.

488
00:21:53,437 --> 00:21:55,314
You have school early tomorrow. Go on.

489
00:21:55,397 --> 00:21:57,065
- Mm, okay.
- Okay.

490
00:22:03,864 --> 00:22:05,365
- Atoy.
- Hmm?

491
00:22:06,116 --> 00:22:07,492
Thank you.

492
00:22:08,118 --> 00:22:10,537
You're really encouraging her to study.

493
00:22:11,038 --> 00:22:13,790
I've wanted that for her for a long time.

494
00:22:13,874 --> 00:22:15,751
Turns out you're the one
who can make it happen,

495
00:22:15,834 --> 00:22:17,127
so she can enroll.

496
00:22:17,961 --> 00:22:20,881
Well, better than just hanging
around here and bothering us, right?

497
00:22:23,008 --> 00:22:27,220
You've done more
than her real parents ever did.

498
00:22:28,930 --> 00:22:31,892
Ame, isn't she looking for…

499
00:22:31,975 --> 00:22:33,685
her real parents?

500
00:22:34,519 --> 00:22:36,438
Doesn't she want to know them?

501
00:22:38,106 --> 00:22:40,692
She asked once.

502
00:22:41,193 --> 00:22:44,613
But not to probe or search further.

503
00:22:45,906 --> 00:22:48,450
Ibyang grew up in the orphanage.

504
00:22:49,242 --> 00:22:51,745
She had no concept of parents.

505
00:22:52,704 --> 00:22:57,084
She knows the words
"family, mother, and father".

506
00:22:57,584 --> 00:22:59,628
But she never experienced them.

507
00:23:00,462 --> 00:23:03,423
So, how could she look for something

508
00:23:03,507 --> 00:23:06,426
she doesn't know and doesn't understand?

509
00:23:06,510 --> 00:23:08,428
[pensive music playing]

510
00:23:08,512 --> 00:23:13,892
Well, maybe when she grows older
and goes to school,

511
00:23:13,975 --> 00:23:16,436
maybe then she'll look
for her parents, right?

512
00:23:17,020 --> 00:23:20,732
Maybe when that day comes,
she won't be interested anymore.

513
00:23:21,316 --> 00:23:22,234
Why not?

514
00:23:22,901 --> 00:23:26,822
Because in her mind,
you're already her parent.

515
00:23:26,905 --> 00:23:30,158
With all the good things
you've done for her.

516
00:23:31,034 --> 00:23:33,120
She won't forget that, Atoy.

517
00:23:33,995 --> 00:23:39,209
[sentimental music playing]

518
00:23:43,463 --> 00:23:47,008
[tense music playing]

519
00:23:49,594 --> 00:23:53,223
You have no right to keep
my child away from me!

520
00:23:53,306 --> 00:23:54,057
[Audrey] What?

521
00:23:54,141 --> 00:23:56,518
[Audrey] <i>You just gave her away</i>
<i>like a cat, is that it?!</i>

522
00:23:57,102 --> 00:23:59,938
Oh, no, no, no, no, no! Don't sit there.

523
00:24:00,522 --> 00:24:01,815
- [woman] <i>Good morning, Sister.</i>
- ["Mr. Tailor" playing]

524
00:24:01,898 --> 00:24:06,528
Why do the nun's hands
look like a man's hands?

525
00:24:06,611 --> 00:24:08,405
Oh, goodness, child!

526
00:24:08,488 --> 00:24:09,739
[both grunt]

527
00:24:09,823 --> 00:24:11,575
- [in English] This is all your fault!
- [Red] I know, I know!

528
00:24:11,658 --> 00:24:13,577
[Red] <i>That's why I'm fixing it, right?!</i>

529
00:24:13,660 --> 00:24:17,080
Sister May! Armed men have entered!

530
00:24:17,164 --> 00:24:19,624
[nun] <i>They pointed guns at Sister Ludy!</i>

531
00:24:19,708 --> 00:24:20,834
UP NEXT

532
00:24:20,917 --> 00:24:22,460
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor…</i> ♪

533
00:24:22,544 --> 00:24:24,713
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

534
00:24:24,796 --> 00:24:27,716
♪ <i>One cut, and it's settled</i> ♪

535
00:24:27,799 --> 00:24:29,759
♪ <i>Fix it</i> ♪
